    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_306ca807",
      "file_path": "catalog-be/src/main/resources/import/tosca/data-types/dataTypes.yml",
      "patchset_number": 27,
      "line": 1401,
      "message": "@Michael, I believe it's a legacy from tosca nfv profile.\nBut because neither ONAP R2 DM or SOL001 has ever defined this, I don't expect the VNF providers would use this property when they're creating VNFD templates.\n\nIf we can't remove this due to backward compatibility, we should at least mark this 'required: false' so when VNF provider creates VNFD based on ONAP R2 DM, they won't create a VNFD which doesn't seem 'valid' due to this mandatory property.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 309,
        "name": "Lianhao Lu",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "llh_misc@outlook.com",
        "username": "LianhaoLu"
      },
      "updated": "2018-09-20 07:28:34.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a76adc5_505cc47c",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_3043486d",
      "file_path": "catalog-be/src/main/resources/import/tosca/data-types/dataTypes.yml",
      "patchset_number": 27,
      "line": 1427,
      "message": "Again, this property is not defined by any DM, nor ONAP R2 neither SOL001. So I don't expect any VNF providers would use this property when they're creating VNFD templates. But since it is an optional property, I think we're ok to keep this for backward compatibility.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 309,
        "name": "Lianhao Lu",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "llh_misc@outlook.com",
        "username": "LianhaoLu"
      },
      "updated": "2018-09-20 07:28:34.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a76adc5_f056305b",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_1075ecc9",
      "file_path": "catalog-be/src/main/resources/import/tosca/data-types/dataTypes.yml",
      "patchset_number": 27,
      "line": 1446,
      "message": "I think according to TOSCA spec, every data type is by default derived from tosca.datatypes.Root.\n\nHere we don't change the derivation, we just make the default explicitly expressed.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 309,
        "name": "Lianhao Lu",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "llh_misc@outlook.com",
        "username": "LianhaoLu"
      },
      "updated": "2018-09-20 07:28:34.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a76adc5_b04c38c9",
      "unresolved": false
    },
